text.section:
This section does not apply to:
Emergency use of a handheld telephone, including calls to:
A 9-1-1 system;
A hospital;
An ambulance service provider;
A fire department;
A law enforcement agency; or
A first aid squad;
Use of a handheld telephone by the following individuals when acting within the scope of official duty:
Law enforcement personnel; and
Emergency personnel;
Use of a handheld telephone as a text messaging device as defined in § 21-1124.1 of this subtitle; and
Use of a handheld telephone as a communication device utilizing push-to-talk technology by an individual operating a commercial motor vehicle, as defined in 49 CFR Part 390.5 of the Federal Motor Carrier Safety Regulations.
